DataElement.preferredName: Differential In-Gel Electrophoresis Electrophoresis Gel TIFF Image java.lang.Object
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A form of gel electrophoresis where up to three different protein samples can be labeled with fluorescent dyes prior to two-dimensional electrophoresis in the same gel. After the gel electrophoresis, the gel is scanned with the excitation wavelength of each dye and the imges are superimposed, allowing detection of changes in protein abundance between samples.:A gel matrix through which molecules are separated, usually by size or charge, under the influence of an electrical field._A bitmap graphics file format utilizing tagged fields.:Any record of an imaging event whether physical or electronic._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is the root of the class hierarchy used as a superclass for all classes.
